# Parameters
batch_size = 32
img_height = 224
img_width = 224
num_classes = 7 # Change this to match the number of classes in your dataset
learning_rate = 1e-4
epochs = 15
dropout_rate = 0.5  # Adjust dropout rate to balance regularization

# Load Training and Validation Datasets with Data Augmentation
train_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/train_dir', # Path to training data
    label_mode='categorical', # Use 'categorical' if labels are one-hot encoded
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=True
)

val_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/val_dir', # Path to validation data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=True
)

# Data Augmentation for the Training Dataset
data_augmentation = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.RandomFlip('horizontal'),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomRotation(0.2),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomZoom(0.2)
])

# Apply data augmentation to the training dataset
train_ds = train_ds.map(lambda x, y: (data_augmentation(x, training=True), y))

# Load Pretrained ResNet50 Model without the Top Classification Layers
base_model = ResNet50(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(img_height, img_width, 3))
base_model.trainable = False # Freeze the base model initially

# Add Custom Classification Layers on Top
x = base_model.output
x = GlobalMaxPooling2D()(x)
x = Dense(1024, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(dropout_rate)(x)  # Add dropout for regularization
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(dropout_rate)(x)  # Add dropout for regularization
output = Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')(x) # Use softmax for multi-class classification
In[4]:
# Define the Model
model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=output)

# Compile the Model
model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=learning_rate),
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Model Summary
model.summary()

import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, classification_report

# Load Test Dataset (Assuming a separate test directory)
test_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/test_dir',  # Path to test data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=False  # Don't shuffle test data, we want consistent evaluation
)

# Evaluate the model on the Test Set
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_ds)
print(f"Test Accuracy: {test_accuracy * 100:.2f}%")

# Metrics Evaluation (Precision, Recall, F1 Score) on Test Set
y_true_test = np.concatenate([y for x, y in test_ds], axis=0)
y_true_test = np.argmax(y_true_test, axis=1)

# Get predictions for the test dataset
y_pred_probs_test = model.predict(test_ds)
y_pred_test = np.argmax(y_pred_probs_test, axis=1)

# Calculate metrics
accuracy_test = accuracy_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test)
precision_test = precision_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
recall_test = recall_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
f1_test = f1_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')

print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Precision: {precision_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Recall: {recall_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test F1 Score: {f1_test * 100:.2f}%")

# Classification Report for Test Set
print("\nTest Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_true_test, y_pred_test))

from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, classification_report

# Load Test Dataset (Assuming a separate test directory)

    'base_dir/test_dir',  # Path to test data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),

)

# Evaluate the model on the Test Set

# Metrics Evaluation (Precision, Recall, F1 Score) on Test Set
y_true_test = np.concatenate([y for x, y in test_ds], axis=0)
y_true_test = np.argmax(y_true_test, axis=1)

# Get predictions for the test dataset
y_pred_probs_test = model.predict(test_ds)
y_pred_test = np.argmax(y_pred_probs_test, axis=1)

# Calculate metrics
accuracy_test = accuracy_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test)
precision_test = precision_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
recall_test = recall_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
f1_test = f1_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')

print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Precision: {precision_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Recall: {recall_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test F1 Score: {f1_test * 100:.2f}%")

# Classification Report for Test Set
print("\nTest Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_true_test, y_pred_test))

import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, classification_report

# Load Test Dataset (Assuming a separate test directory)
test_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/test_dir',  # Path to test data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=False  # Don't shuffle test data, we want consistent evaluation
)

# Evaluate the model on the Test Set
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_ds)
print(f"Test Accuracy: {test_accuracy * 100:.2f}%")

# Metrics Evaluation (Precision, Recall, F1 Score) on Test Set
y_true_test = np.concatenate([y for x, y in test_ds], axis=0)
y_true_test = np.argmax(y_true_test, axis=1)

# Get predictions for the test dataset
y_pred_probs_test = model.predict(test_ds)
y_pred_test = np.argmax(y_pred_probs_test, axis=1)

# Calculate metrics
accuracy_test = accuracy_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test)
precision_test = precision_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
recall_test = recall_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
f1_test = f1_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')

print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Precision: {precision_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Recall: {recall_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test F1 Score: {f1_test * 100:.2f}%")

# Classification Report for Test Set
print("\nTest Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_true_test, y_pred_test))

    'base_dir/train_dir', # Path to training data
    label_mode='categorical', # Use 'categorical' if labels are one-hot encoded
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=True
)

val_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/val_dir', # Path to validation data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=True
)

# Data Augmentation for the Training Dataset
data_augmentation = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.RandomFlip('horizontal'),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomRotation(0.2),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomZoom(0.2)
])

# Apply data augmentation to the training dataset
train_ds = train_ds.map(lambda x, y: (data_augmentation(x, training=True), y))

import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, classification_report

# Load Test Dataset (Assuming a separate test directory)
test_ds = image_dataset_from_directory(
    'base_dir/test_dir',  # Path to test data
    label_mode='categorical',
    batch_size=batch_size,
    image_size=(img_height, img_width),
    shuffle=False  # Don't shuffle test data, we want consistent evaluation
)

# Evaluate the model on the Test Set
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_ds)
print(f"Test Accuracy: {test_accuracy * 100:.2f}%")

# Metrics Evaluation (Precision, Recall, F1 Score) on Test Set
y_true_test = np.concatenate([y for x, y in test_ds], axis=0)
y_true_test = np.argmax(y_true_test, axis=1)

# Get predictions for the test dataset
y_pred_probs_test = model.predict(test_ds)
y_pred_test = np.argmax(y_pred_probs_test, axis=1)

# Calculate metrics
accuracy_test = accuracy_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test)
precision_test = precision_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
recall_test = recall_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')
f1_test = f1_score(y_true_test, y_pred_test, average='weighted')

print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Precision: {precision_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Recall: {recall_test * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test F1 Score: {f1_test * 100:.2f}%")

# Classification Report for Test Set
print("\nTest Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_true_test, y_pred_test))

x = Dropout(dropout_rate)(x)  # Add dropout for regularization
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(dropout_rate)(x)  # Add dropout for regularization
